bilingual.source: When the wind is in the east, then the fish bite the least.
bilingual.target: 当风在东边时，鱼咬得最少。
这本书是我最少喜欢的。

bilingual.source: The least you could do is apologize.
bilingual.target: 你最少能做的就是道歉。

bilingual.source: This dish needs the least amount of salt.
This is the least I can do to help you.
bilingual.target: 这是我能帮你的最少的事情。

bilingual.source: He is the one who talks the least among us.
bilingual.target: 他是我们中最少说话的人。

bilingual.source: This is the least expensive option available.
bilingual.target: 这是可用的最少的花费选项。

bilingual.source: This issue is the least important of all.
bilingual.target: 这个问题是所有问题中最少重要的。

bilingual.source: You should spend the least time on this task.
bilingual.target: 你应该花最少的时间在这件事上。

bilingual.source: He did the least amount of work but got the most credit.
bilingual.target: 他做的工作最少，但得到了最多的赞誉。

list.abstract: least（英 [liːst]，美 [liːst]），英语单词，作限定词为最少；最小；最不重要。作形容词为最少的；最小的；最不重要的。作副词为最少；至少。短语搭配有at least（至少）、last but not least（最后的但并非最不重要的）。例句为“That, at least, is the hope（这至少是希望）”。 least相关近义词有lowest、minimum等，相关反义词有most。

yingyinNormal.en: And the channels you're least investing in are adding enormous value in segments that currently appear to have low value but actually have the highest spending potential.
yingyinNormal.zh: 吸引投资最少，投入了巨大财力的环节，现在看来创造的价值却是最少的，但实际上有很高的消费潜力。

yingyinNormal.en: It seems the most expensive place you're advertising is actually bringing you the customers who are spending the least.
yingyinNormal.zh: 似乎你广告做得最贵的，它所带来的顾客却是最少的。

yingyinNormal.en: And I've done what I can on my own by requiring federal contractors to pay their workers at least ten-ten an hour.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我已经做了我能做得事情，要求联邦的承包商支付给他们员工的工资最少是每小时$10.10。

yingyinNormal.en: I myself know of at least 58 techniques to refine a seemingly infinite array of randomly generated possibilities down to the smallest number of feasible variables.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我就至少知道58种方法可以把看似无穷的随机生成的可能性精简到最少，使变量具备可行性。

yingyinNormal.en: Mayor Emanuel in Chicago and Mayor Garcetti in L.A. are working to lift their cities' wages over time to at least thirteen dollars an hour.
yingyinNormal.zh: 芝加哥的伊曼纽尔市长和洛杉矶的贾西狄市长都在努力提高工资标准，他们将加班工资提高到了最少13美元每小时。

yingyinNormal.en: This is the optimal arrangement to dry with the least amount of paper. Again, shake your hands 12 times, fold, and dry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是用最少量的纸，达到最佳的干手方式 再看一次，甩手12下，对折再擦干。

yingyinNormal.en: At least we have each other.
yingyinNormal.zh: 至少我们还在一起。

yingyinNormal.en: To say the least of what we do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们所做的还远不止此。

yingyinNormal.en: At least we didn't have Instagram.
yingyinNormal.zh: 至少我们当时没有Instagram。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: Well, at least that's a great suit.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这件外套很好看。

yingyinNormal.en: The fel. Or at least it's influence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是恶魔，或者至少是受他影响。

yingyinNormal.en: Chat? we don't chat. at least not offline.
yingyinNormal.zh: 聊天？我们平时不聊天，至少下了网不聊。

yingyinNormal.en: Can't you at least put your phones on vibrate?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们至少可以手机调成震动吗?

yingyinNormal.en: Well at least I can take this silly thing off.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那我就能把这该死的东西摘下了。

yingyinNormal.en: This is killing her. At least something's dying.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这简直要让她气死了，至少有什么要死掉了。

yingyinNormal.en: No, it's not that. At least, it's not only that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，不是因为这个，还有别的原因。

yingyinNormal.en: At least from that little town we both call home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 至少不用再被束缚在那个我们称之为家的小镇。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, at least she had some silence once in awhile.
yingyinNormal.zh: 被关在里面的女的偶尔还能"沉默"[清静]一会呢。

yingyinNormal.en: I kinda scared myself. Well, at least you scared someone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我吓到自己了。那起码有吓到人。

yingyinNormal.en: Amanda's needling takes several hours, half a day at least.
yingyinNormal.zh: 阿曼达的针术需要几小时至少半天才能见效。

exam_freq_info.chinese: 最少; 至少; 最小

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Mechanization isn't the answer, either – not yet, at <highlight>least</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 机械化也不是解决问题的办法——至少目前还不是。

examination_example.sentence: In the internet age, at <highlight>least</highlight> in theory, this fraction can be much reduced.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在互联网时代，至少在理论上，这一比例可以大大降低。

examination_example.sentence: You should write at <highlight>least</highlight> 150 words.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你应该写至少150个单词。

sense_info_list.en: to the smallest extent or degree；smallest in amount, extent, or significance
sense_info_list.zh: 最少; 至少; 最小

examination_example.sentence: Millennials, it seems, face the paradox of being the <highlight>least</highlight> formal generation yet the most conscious of style and personal branding.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 千禧一代似乎面临这样一种悖论：一方面，他们是最率性随意的一代，另一方面，他们却又是对时尚和个人品牌最讲究的一代。

examination_example.sentence: 70 a week, one of the <highlight>least</highlight> generous in the EU.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每周70英镑，是欧盟最不慷慨的一次。

examination_example.sentence: Look up Homo sapiens, and you will read: "Listed as <highlight>Least</highlight> Concern as the species is very widely distributed, adaptable, currently increasing. "
examination_example.sentence_trans: 查阅“智人”这一词条，你将会读到：“属于非危物种，因为该物种分布很广，适应性强，目前数量呈上升趋势。”

word_usage.usage:
least of all表示“最不，根本不”，位于句首时需要将助动词提前，如：
Least of all do I like that book.
我最不喜欢那本书。
not (in) the least表示“一点也不”，后常接形容词，如“be not the least interested一点也不感兴趣”。

sense_info_list.en: to the smallest extent or degree

examination_example.sentence: Last but not <highlight>least</highlight>, laws and regulations with clear penalties should be implemented and enforced.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最后但同样重要的是，具有明确惩罚措施的法律法规应该得到实施和执行。

examination_example.sentence: This suggests that these behaviors may, at <highlight>least</highlight> in part, explain the link.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这表明这些行为至少部分解释了这种联系存在的原因。

examination_example.sentence: How often his fellow researchers in psychology and neuroscience make what he believes are erroneous—or at <highlight>least</highlight> premature—causal connections between music and intelligence?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他在心理学和神经科学领域的同事们会在音乐和智力之间建立他认为是错误的或至少是过早的因果关系，这种情况有多频繁呢？

examination_example.sentence: But there's no denying ethical leadership is at <highlight>least</highlight> a critical step in the right direction.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但不可否认，有道德的领导至少是朝着正确方向迈出的关键一步。

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 最后的但并非最不重要的

examination_example.sentence: They usually work on computers at school for at <highlight>least</highlight> two hours during the day.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们通常白天在学校用电脑工作至少两个小时。

examination_example.sentence: The other ten percent use it at <highlight>least</highlight> three or four times a week.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另外10%的人每周至少使用三到四次。

examination_example.sentence: There was just one requirement: Lin would have to promise to study it for at <highlight>least</highlight> one year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 只有一个要求:林必须承诺至少学习一年。

examination_example.sentence: Now, Tokyo is about one third more expensive than Karachi, which is the <highlight>least</highlight> expensive city among the 214 cities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 现在，东京比卡拉奇贵三分之一左右，卡拉奇是214个城市中最不贵的城市。

examination_example.sentence: They may find nothing unusual in their bodies and feel <highlight>least</highlight> uncomfortable at first.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 起初，他们可能不会发现身体有什么异常，也不会感到不舒服。

examination_example.sentence: Milk is also sugar-free because it is the <highlight>least</highlight> fattening.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 牛奶也是无糖的，因为它是最不容易发胖的。

examination_example.sentence: Last but not <highlight>least</highlight>, students there have colorful activities and I hope the school life will be wonderful there.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最后但同样重要的是，那里的学生有丰富多彩的活动，我希望那里的学校生活会很精彩。

examination_example.sentence: The forest floor is the lowest layer full of animal life and receives the <highlight>least</highlight> amount of light.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 森林地面是充满动物生命的最低层，接受的光线最少。

examination_example.sentence: Last but not <highlight>least</highlight>，the government should make laws to guide people's behavior．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最后但同样重要的是，政府应该制定法律来指导人们的行为。

word_usage.usage:
least不仅是little“少”的最高级形式，还可以协助构成否定式的最高级，表示“最不……”。
如：I don’t have enough money,so I will buy the least expensive car.
我没有足够的钱，所以我会买那辆最便宜的车。
